modules.description: Generates Huffman trees from symbol frequency distributions using priority queues and recursive merging. Operates on lists of (symbol, frequency) pairs and produces a tree structure with encoded paths. Used to create efficient encoding schemes for data compression tasks.

Provides operations to compare, combine, and sort Huffman trees, and to construct a Huffman tree from symbol-frequency pairs. Works with labeled binary trees where nodes contain arbitrary data and leaves represent symbols. Used to generate and visualize Huffman encoding structures for data compression tasks.
